Patch 1: navigator polyfill
===========================

Add navigator polyfill to bundle_loader.js before the Telegram bundle loads.
GramJS checks navigator.onLine when deciding whether to reconnect.
Pebble's JS runtime has no navigator object.

File: src/pkjs/lib/bundle_loader.js
-------------------------------------

After the window.location polyfill block (line 13) and before the
`try { require('./telegram-bundle.js');` line (line 15), insert:

    // Polyfill navigator for GramJS reconnection logic
    if (typeof navigator === 'undefined') {
        globalThis.navigator = { onLine: true, userAgent: 'Clawd PKJS' };
    } else if (typeof window !== 'undefined' && !window.navigator) {
        window.navigator = globalThis.navigator;
    }

Verification:
- Build with `pebble build` — should compile without errors
- Check logs for any "navigator is not defined" errors
- GramJS should believe it's always online and attempt reconnections normally